-- U.S. Exim Bank to Lend South Africa $2 Billion for Clean Energy
-- B y   A n d r e s   R .   M a r t i n e z
-- 2012-08-07T11:57:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-07/u-s-exim-bank-to-lend-south-africa-2-billion-for-clean-energy.html
The U.S. Export-Import Bank signed an
agreement to lend South Africa’s Industrial Development Corp. $2
billion to fund clean-energy projects, U.S. Secretary of State
 Hillary Clinton  said.  Economic growth in South Africa benefits the rest of the
continent, Clinton told reporters in Pretoria, South Africa’s
capital, today.   To contact the reporter on this story:
Andres R. Martinez in Johannesburg at 
 amartinez28@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
